# 詞：銀包

1. 佢個銀包好厚，裝咗好多現金同信用卡。 (His wallet is very thick, filled with lots of cash and credit cards.)
2. 我哋去食肆之前，一定要檢查下銀包，確保錢唔會遺失。 (Before we go to a restaurant, we must check our wallet to make sure the money won't be lost.)
3. 佢個銀包好舊，已經用咗好多年，但仲係好實用。 (His wallet is quite old, having been used for many years, but it is still very practical.)
4. 我哋應該將重要文件同銀包分開放，以免一齊弄丟。 (We should keep important documents and the wallet separate to avoid losing them together.)
5. 佢個銀包好輕，裝咗好多東西都唔覺得重。 (His wallet is very light; even though it's filled with many things, it doesn't feel heavy.)
6. 我哋應該養成習慣，每次用完銀包都要收好，唔好隨地亂丟。 (We should develop the habit of putting away our wallet properly after use, not leaving it lying around.)
7. 佢個銀包好整齊，每一張紙幣都摺得整齊。 (His wallet is very neat; every bill is folded neatly.)
8. 我哋應該定期檢查銀包，確保冇遺失咗任何重要物品。 (We should regularly check our wallet to ensure no important items have been lost.)
9. 佢個銀包好貴，係用真皮製成，好有質感。 (His wallet is quite expensive, made of genuine leather, and has a very high-quality feel.)
10. 我哋應該將銀包放喺安全嘅地方，唔好放喺容易被人偷嘅位置。 (We should keep our wallet in a safe place, not in a location where it's easy for someone to steal.) [end of text]


